-- Indian Renewable Energy Sells $89 Million in Bonds; Yields at 8.87%-9.02%
-- B y   S u p r o t i p   G h o s h
-- 2010-09-28T10:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/indian-renewable-energy-sells-89-million-in-bonds-yields-at-8-87-9-02-.html
Indian Renewable Energy Development
Agency Ltd., a state-owned lender, is said to have raised 4
billion rupees ($88.7 million) from the sale of 10- and 15-year
bonds, according to two people familiar with the issue.  The New Delhi-based lender raised 1.5 billion rupees from
10-year bonds paying 8.87 percent and sold 2.5 billion rupees of
15-year bonds at 9.02 percent, said the people, who asked not to
be identified as the information is private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suprotip Ghosh in Mumbai 
 sghosh47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will McSheehy at   wmcsheehy@bloomberg.net . 